cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.RO

The paper discusses the use of recurrent neural networks for abstraction tasks in multi-modal data, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the use of multiple time-scale recurrent models, which are a type of neural network commonly used in natural language processing (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of multi-modal data from robot manipulation tasks (cs.RO) and includes a study on image data (cs.CV).
